## How the sliding window works (visual)

```
Timeline ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────▶
                        │◄────── windowMs (60 s) ──────►│
                        │                               │
                        windowStart                    now
                             ↑       ↑   ↑   ↑   ↑    ↑
                          pruned   kept kept kept kept NEW

  Fixed window:  resets the counter at a hard clock boundary → client can
                 burst maxRequests just before AND just after the boundary.

  Sliding window: the window *follows* `now`, so the full windowMs always
                  separates the oldest kept request from the current time.
                  No boundary to exploit.
```

